# Real-Time Collaborative Text Editor

This project is a **real-time collaborative text editor** built using **React**, **Tiptap**, **Yjs**, and **WebRTC**. It allows multiple users to edit the same document simultaneously with real-time synchronization, user attribution, and collaborative editing.

## Features

- **Real-Time Collaboration:** Multiple users can edit the same document at the same time.
- **User Attribution:** Each user's edits are color-coded and displayed with their name.
- **WebRTC Integration:** Uses **Yjs** and **WebRTC** to handle real-time collaboration and data synchronization.
- **Avatar Support:** Users can upload an avatar during login to personalize their identity.
- **Responsive Design:** The UI adapts across devices using Tailwind CSS for flexible, responsive layouts.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend:**
  - **React**: A JavaScript library for building user interfaces.
  - **Tiptap**: A rich-text editor framework for building text editors in React.
  - **Tailwind CSS**: A utility-first CSS framework for styling the application.
  
- **Real-Time Collaboration:**
  - **Yjs**: A framework for building collaborative applications with real-time data synchronization.
  - **WebRTC**: A protocol for peer-to-peer communication, enabling real-time syncing between users.
  
- **State Management:**
  - **React Hooks**: Managing state using React's built-in hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`).

- **Other Libraries:**
  - **uuid**: For generating unique identifiers for users.

## Installation Guide

Follow these steps to set up and run the project locally.

### Prerequisites

- **Node.js**: Ensure you have Node.js installed. You can download it from [here](https://nodejs.org/).
- **npm**: The Node.js package manager should be installed alongside Node.js.

### Setup Instructions

1. **Clone the Repository:**

   Clone the repository to your local machine using Git:

